commit.title: [dune] Add a shim for calling `coqtop`.
commit.message:
[dune] Add a shim for calling `coqtop`.

This is a bit of hack as requested by @Skyskimmer, but it should
indeed help developers.

The current implementation is quite hacky so I am sure it can be
improved, it also breaks when the stdlib is not present, but I wasn't
able to cook an `(enabled_if ...)` field for it to work.
